{"id": 3472, "title": "Ticket #3472: Condor-C should record the submit job ID", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen Condor-C submits a job to a remote Condor system, it's difficult to tie the remote job to the corresponding job in the schedd from the remote side.\n\n<p>Let's say we're submitting from submitter.ucsd.edu to ce.unl.edu.  If I think job 1234 on ce.unl.edu is having an issue, I know the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=SubmitterId\" title=\"Submitter Id\">SubmitterId</a></span> (\"submitter.ucsd.edu\") to track the remote schedd.  However, I don't know the submitter's job id.\n\n</p><p>I propose that Condor-C should write the following attribute:\n\n</p><p><span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=SubmitterGlobalJobId\" title=\"Submitter Global Job Id\">SubmitterGlobalJobId</a></span> = \"submitter.ucsd.edu#5678#123...\"\n\n</p><p>into the submit ad.  This is actually quite similar to what the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=JobRouter\" title=\"Job Router\">JobRouter</a></span> does.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Oct-20 16:52</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=46053\">[46053]</a></span>: Add new job attribute <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=SubmitterGlobalJobId\" title=\"Submitter Global Job Id\">SubmitterGlobalJobId</a></span> for Condor-C. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=3472\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3472'); return false;\" title=\"Condor-C should record the submit job ID\">#3472</a></span> <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=SubmitterGlobalJobId\" title=\"Submitter Global Job Id\">SubmitterGlobalJobId</a></span> is set in the new job to match the value of <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=GlobalJobId\" title=\"Global Job Id\">GlobalJobId</a></span> in the original job.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Oct-20 16:52</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=46054\">[46054]</a></span>: Docs for new job attribute <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=SubmitterGlobalJobId\" title=\"Submitter Global Job Id\">SubmitterGlobalJobId</a></span>. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=3472\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3472'); return false;\" title=\"Condor-C should record the submit job ID\">#3472</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2015-Oct-20 16:53", "status": "resolved", "created": "2013-Jan-31 14:44", "fixed_version": "2013-Jan-31 14:44", "broken_version": "", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "Grid", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "#4555", "creator": "bbockelm", "rust": "", "customer_group": "osg", "visibility": "public", "notify": "bbockelm@cse.unl.edu blin@cs.wisc.edu", "due_date": ""}